rounded-[18px] px-4 py-1.5 data-[multiline]:py-3 max-w-[var(--user-chat-width,70%)]" data-multiline=""><div class="whitespace-pre-wrap">In this assignment, you will build a small, GitHub-ready Python project that cleans a messy sales dataset. The final result should be something you would be comfortable linking on your resume or showing to a recruiter.

You will:

Write a Python script with clear comments describing your data cleaning steps.
Use GitHub Copilot to generate part of your function code (and then refine it).
Run and test your script to make sure it works end-to-end.
Write a short reflection explaining what Copilot generated, what you modified, and what you learned.
Goal: One focused, complete mini-project that demonstrates data cleaning, basic Python, and responsible use of AI coding tools.

2. Files and Dataset
The core of this assignment is one messy CSV file and one Python script.

Provided File (in Canvas)
sales_data_raw.csv  messy sales data with inconsistent column names, whitespace, missing values, and invalid numbers. 
Download sales_data_raw.csv here Download hereand place it in the path shown below inside your project:

ism2411-data-cleaning-copilot/
 data/
     raw/
         sales_data_raw.csv
You do not need to modify this file manually. All cleaning should happen in Python.

3. Repository Setup (Minimal but Professional)
Create a new GitHub repository named exactly:

ism2411-data-cleaning-copilot
Inside the repo, create this minimal required structure:

ism2411-data-cleaning-copilot/
 data/
    raw/
       sales_data_raw.csv
    processed/
        sales_data_clean.csv        # created by your script
 src/
    data_cleaning.py                # your main script
 README.md                           # short project description
 reflection.md                       # your written explanation
        
Make at least 35 small, meaningful commits instead of one giant commit at the end.

4. Step 1  Write data_cleaning.py with Comments
Create a file at src/data_cleaning.py. This file should:

Import the libraries you need (for example, pandas as pd).
Load sales_data_raw.csv from data/raw/.
Apply a small, clear sequence of cleaning steps.
Write the cleaned data to data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv.
Required Cleaning Steps (Minimum)
Your script must do at least all of the following:

Standardize column names (for example, lowercase and underscores).
Strip leading/trailing whitespace from product names and categories.
Handle missing prices and quantities (drop or fill  but be consistent).
Remove rows with clearly invalid values (negative quantity, negative price).
Comment Requirements
At the top of the file, add a short comment explaining the overall purpose of the script.
Before each major step, include a comment describing:
What you are doing (for example, remove negative quantities).
Why you are doing it (for example, negative quantities are data entry errors).
5. Step 2  Use GitHub Copilot to Generate Function Code
You must use GitHub Copilot to generate at least two functions in data_cleaning.py.

Examples (you may use these names or your own):

def load_data(file_path: str):
    ...

def clean_column_names(df):
    ...

def handle_missing_values(df):
    ...

def remove_invalid_rows(df):
    ...
Above each Copilot-assisted function, write a clear comment describing what the function should do.
Trigger Copilot, review the suggestion, and accept/modify it.
You are expected to change something in Copilots suggestion (names, logic, or structure) so that it truly fits your design.
Remember: Copilot is a starting point. You are graded on how you use it, not on accepting its first suggestion.

6. Step 3  Run and Test Your Script
Add this block to the bottom of data_cleaning.py so you can run the pipeline directly:

if __name__ == "__main__":
    raw_path = "data/raw/sales_data_raw.csv"
    cleaned_path = "data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv"

    df_raw = load_data(raw_path)
    df_clean = clean_column_names(df_raw)
    df_clean = handle_missing_values(df_clean)
    df_clean = remove_invalid_rows(df_clean)
    df_clean.to_csv(cleaned_path, index=False)
    print("Cleaning complete. First few rows:")
    print(df_clean.head())
From your project root folder, run:

python src/data_cleaning.py
Make sure that:

No errors are thrown.
data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv is created.
The preview printed to the terminal looks cleaner than the raw file (no obvious negative quantities, etc.).
7. Step 4  Write reflection.md
Create a file named reflection.md in the root of your repository. In 35 paragraphs, answer the following prompts:

What Copilot generated
Which functions or code blocks came primarily from Copilots suggestions? How did you prompt it (comments, partial code, etc.)?
What you modified
What changes did you make to Copilots code (renaming variables, changing logic, simplifying steps)? Why were those changes needed?
What you learned
What did you learn about data cleaning in Python and about using Copilot as a tool (strengths and limitations)? Include at least one specific example.
8. Deliverables and Grading
What You Submit
A GitHub repository named ism2411-data-cleaning-copilot that includes:
src/data_cleaning.py
data/raw/sales_data_raw.csv
data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv
README.md (short description and run instructions)
reflection.md
In Canvas: the URL to your GitHub repository.
Quick Self-Check: If a recruiter clicked your GitHub link and opened this repo, would they (1) see code that runs, (2) understand what it does from your comments and README, and (3) see a short reflection of how you used Copilot? If yes, you are in good shape.

Grading Breakdown
Code &amp; Cleaning Logic (35%)  Script runs, produces a cleaned CSV, and implements the required steps.
Comments &amp; Clarity (20%)  Cleaning steps are clearly described and justified in comments.
Copilot Use (20%)  At least two functions clearly originated from Copilot and were meaningfully modified.
Reflection (15%)  Answers the three questions with specific examples.
GitHub Packaging (10%)  Correct repo name, basic README, and sensible commit history.</div></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex justify-end"><div class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-python"><span><span><span class="hljs-string">"""
data_cleaning.py
----------------
Purpose:
    This script loads a messy sales dataset, applies a sequence of data cleaning
    steps, and exports a cleaned CSV file. The goal is to demonstrate a clear,
    professional data-cleaning pipeline suitable for a resume-ready GitHub portfolio.

Cleaning performed:
    - Standardize column names
    - Strip whitespace from product/category fields
    - Handle missing values consistently
    - Remove invalid negative prices/quantities
"""</span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">import</span></span><span> pandas </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">as</span></span><span> pd

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Function: load_data</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># What it does:</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">#   Loads the raw CSV file into a DataFrame.</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Why:</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">#   Separating this step makes the script cleaner and testable.</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">load_data</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">file_path: <span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df


</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Function: clean_column_names</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># What it does:</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">#   Standardizes column names to lowercase with underscores.</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Why:</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">#   Consistent naming avoids bugs and improves readability.</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">clean_column_names</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    df.columns = (
        df.columns
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.lower()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">" "</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"-"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
    )
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df


</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Function: handle_missing_values</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># What it does:</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">#   Handles missing prices/quantities by dropping rows where both are missing,</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">#   and filling remaining missing numeric values with zero.</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Why:</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">#   Missing numeric values can break analyses; this is a consistent strategy.</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">handle_missing_values</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Drop rows where BOTH price and quantity are missing</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">and</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df.dropna(subset=[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span>], how=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"all"</span></span><span>)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Fill remaining missing numeric values with 0</span></span><span>
    num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"number"</span></span><span>).columns
    df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(</span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df


</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Function: remove_invalid_rows</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># What it does:</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">#   Removes rows with negative prices or negative quantities.</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Why:</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment">#   These represent invalid data entry errors.</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">remove_invalid_rows</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()

    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]

    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]

    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df


</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Main cleaning pipeline</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># --------------------------------------------------------------</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> __name__ == </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"__main__"</span></span><span>:
    raw_path = </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"data/raw/sales_data_raw.csv"</span></span><span>
    cleaned_path = </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv"</span></span><span>

    df_raw = load_data(raw_path)
    df_clean = clean_column_names(df_raw)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Strip whitespace from text fields</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">for</span></span><span> col </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df_clean.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"object"</span></span><span>).columns:
        df_clean[col] = df_clean[col].</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip()

    df_clean = handle_missing_values(df_clean)
    df_clean = remove_invalid_rows(df_clean)

    df_clean.to_csv(cleaned_path, index=</span><span><span class="hljs-literal">False</span></span><span>)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"Cleaning complete. First few rows:"</span></span><span>)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(df_clean.head())
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>

Cleaning Project</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What Copilot Generated</span></span><span>
For this assignment, I used GitHub Copilot to help generate two of the functions inside </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`data_cleaning.py`</span></span><span>:  
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`load_data()`</span></span><span>  
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`clean_column_names()`</span></span><span>  

I prompted Copilot by writing a comment above each function explaining what the function should do. Once the comment was written, Copilot produced a suggested function body that I accepted and then modified.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What I Modified</span></span><span>
Although Copilot generated helpful starting points, I made several changes:

</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**Renamed variables and improved clarity**</span></span><span>: Copilot originally used very short variable names; I rewrote them to be more readable.
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**Strengthened column-cleaning logic**</span></span><span>: The original suggestion did not handle hyphens or extra whitespace. I added </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`.str.replace("-", "_")`</span></span><span> and </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`.str.strip()`</span></span><span>.
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-strong">**Adjusted missing-value handling**</span></span><span>: Copilot attempted to fill all missing values with zero, which isn't always appropriate. I modified the logic so the script drops rows where both price and quantity are missing, while only filling remaining numeric values.

These changes ensured the code followed best practices and aligned with the cleaning requirements.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What I Learned</span></span><span>
This project taught me both technical skills and insights about working with AI tools.

From a data perspective, I learned how important it is to create a repeatable pipeline: clean column names, standardize text, handle missing data consistently, and remove invalid rows. I also learned to carefully inspect edge cases in messy datasetsCopilot cant assume the meaning of missing or negative values, so I had to make those decisions deliberately.

From a Copilot perspective, I learned that it works best when I give it a good scaffold, such as comments or partial code. It saves time on boilerplate but still requires human judgment. For example, Copilot suggested allowing negative prices, which is not correct for sales data. That showed me that Copilot is helpful, but not authoritative.

Overall, this assignment taught me how to mix AI-assisted coding with intentional, thoughtful software development.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>

code</button></div></div></div><div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-python"><span><span><span class="hljs-string">"""
data_cleaning.py
Purpose:
    Loads messy sales data, cleans it, and writes cleaned output to data/processed.
"""</span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">import</span></span><span> pandas </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">as</span></span><span> pd

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted function</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">load_data</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">file_path: <span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted function</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">clean_column_names</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    df.columns = (
        df.columns
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.lower()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">" "</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"-"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
    )
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Handles missing numeric values</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">handle_missing_values</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">and</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df.dropna(subset=[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span>], how=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"all"</span></span><span>)
    num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"number"</span></span><span>).columns
    df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(</span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Removes negative values</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">remove_invalid_rows</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df


</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> __name__ == </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"__main__"</span></span><span>:
    raw_path = </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"data/raw/sales_data_raw.csv"</span></span><span>
    cleaned_path = </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv"</span></span><span>

    df_raw = load_data(raw_path)
    df_clean = clean_column_names(df_raw)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># strip whitespace from text fields</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">for</span></span><span> col </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df_clean.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"object"</span></span><span>).columns:
        df_clean[col] = df_clean[col].</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip()

    df_clean = handle_missing_values(df_clean)
    df_clean = remove_invalid_rows(df_clean)

    df_clean.to_csv(cleaned_path, index=</span><span><span class="hljs-literal">False</span></span><span>)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"Cleaning complete. First few rows:"</span></span><span>)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(df_clean.head())
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>

Cleaning Project</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What Copilot Generated</span></span><span>
Copilot generated the base versions of two functions:
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`load_data()`</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`clean_column_names()`</span></span><span>

I triggered Copilot by writing comments above each function describing what it should do.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What I Modified</span></span><span>
I changed Copilot's code to make it cleaner and more accurate:
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Improved the column-cleaning logic to handle spaces, hyphens, and uppercase letters.
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Adjusted missing-value logic so it only fills numeric values and drops rows missing both price and quantity.
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> Added explicit checks for negative values.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What I Learned</span></span><span>
I learned how to build a reproducible cleaning pipeline in Python: 
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> standardizing column names, 
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> stripping whitespace, 
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> handling missing values, 
</span><span><span class="hljs-bullet">-</span></span><span> and removing invalid rows.

I also learned that Copilot is helpful for writing boilerplate code, but it needs human judgment.  
For example, Copilot suggested filling all missing values with 0, which would have created unrealistic prices.  
This showed me that Copilot speeds up coding, but I still have to guide the logic.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>

turn on Add a README file</strong> when creating the GitHub repo.</p>
<p data-start="86" data-end="97">Heres why:</p>
<h3 data-start="99" data-end="155"> Why you should turn on README during repo creation</h3>
<ul data-start="156" data-end="441">
<li data-start="156" data-end="225">
<p data-start="158" data-end="225">It makes the repo initialize properly (so you can clone it easily).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="226" data-end="305">
<p data-start="228" data-end="305">It avoids GitHub asking you to create a commit before you can upload files.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="306" data-end="441">
<p data-start="308" data-end="441">Its required anyway for this assignment, so starting with a README is fine  you will replace it later with the one I wrote for you.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="443" data-end="467"> What to do exactly</h3>
<p data-start="468" data-end="500">When you create the repo, check:</p>
<p data-start="502" data-end="525"> <strong data-start="504" data-end="525">Add a README file</strong></p>
<p data-start="527" data-end="606">Everything else (like .gitignore or license) can stay off unless you want them.</p>
<hr data-start="608" data-end="611">
<p data-start="613" data-end="695" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">If you'd like, I can walk you through the GitHub creation screen step-by-step too.</p></div></div></div></div><div data_cleaning.py
Purpose:
    Loads messy sales data, cleans it, and writes cleaned output to data/processed.
"""</span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">import</span></span><span> pandas </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">as</span></span><span> pd

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted function</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">load_data</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">file_path: <span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted function</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">clean_column_names</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    df.columns = (
        df.columns
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.lower()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">" "</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"-"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
    )
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Handles missing numeric values</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">handle_missing_values</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">and</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df.dropna(subset=[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span>], how=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"all"</span></span><span>)
    num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"number"</span></span><span>).columns
    df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(</span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Removes negative values</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">remove_invalid_rows</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

    df_raw = load_data(raw_path)
    df_clean = clean_column_names(df_raw)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># strip whitespace from text fields</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">for</span></span><span> col </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df_clean.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"object"</span></span><span>).columns:
        df_clean[col] = df_clean[col].</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip()

    df_clean = handle_missing_values(df_clean)
    df_clean = remove_invalid_rows(df_clean)

    df_clean.to_csv(cleaned_path, index=</span><span><span class="hljs-literal">False</span></span><span>)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"Cleaning complete. First few rows:"</span></span><span>)

data_cleaning.py
Purpose:
    Loads messy sales data, cleans it, and writes cleaned output to data/processed.
"""
import pandas as pd
# Copilot-assisted function
def load_data(file_path: str) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    return df
# Copilot-assisted function
def clean_column_names(df: pd.DataFrame) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    df.columns = (
        df.columns
        .str.strip()
        .str.lower()
        .str.replace(" ", "_")
        .str.replace("-", "_")
    )
    return df
# Handles missing numeric values
def handle_missing_values(df: pd.DataFrame) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    if "price" in df.columns and "quantity" in df.columns:
        df = df.dropna(subset=["price", "quantity"], how="all")
    num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include="number").columns
    df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(0)
    return df

# Removes negative values
def remove_invalid_rows(df):
    # Convert price column to numeric first
    df["price"] = pd.to_numeric(df["price"], errors="coerce")
print(df["price"].dtype)

  
    # Remove rows with missing price
    df = df.dropna(subset=["price"])
    # Remove negative prices
    df = df[df["price"] &gt;= 0]
    return df

if __name__ == "__main__":
    raw_path = "data/raw/sales_data_raw.csv"
    cleaned_path = "data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv"
    df_raw = load_data(raw_path)
    print(df_raw.columns)
    df_clean = clean_column_names(df_raw)
    # strip whitespace from text fields
    for col in df_clean.select_dtypes(include="object").columns:
        df_clean[col] = df_clean[col].str.strip()
    df_clean = handle_missing_values(df_clean)
    df_clean = remove_invalid_rows(df_clean)
    df_clean.to_csv(cleaned_path, index=False)
    print("Cleaning complete. First few rows:")

data_cleaning.py
Purpose:
    Loads messy sales data, cleans it, and writes cleaned output to data/processed.
"""</span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">import</span></span><span> pandas </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">as</span></span><span> pd

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted function</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">load_data</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">file_path: <span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted function</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">clean_column_names</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    df.columns = (
        df.columns
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.lower()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">" "</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"-"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
    )
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Handles missing numeric values</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">handle_missing_values</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">and</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df.dropna(subset=[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span>], how=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"all"</span></span><span>)
    num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"number"</span></span><span>).columns
    df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(</span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Removes negative values</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">remove_invalid_rows</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Convert price column to numeric first</span></span><span>
    df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>] = pd.to_numeric(df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>], errors=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"coerce"</span></span><span>)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Check first few values and type</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>].head(</span><span><span class="hljs-number">10</span></span><span>))
    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>].dtype)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Remove rows with missing price</span></span><span>
    df = df.dropna(subset=[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>])

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Remove negative prices</span></span><span>
    df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Remove negative quantities if column exists</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"quantity"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]

    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df


</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> __name__ == </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"__main__"</span></span><span>:
    raw_path = </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"data/raw/sales_data_raw.csv"</span></span><span>
    cleaned_path = </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv"</span></span><span>

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Load raw data</span></span><span>
    df_raw = load_data(raw_path)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"Columns in CSV:"</span></span><span>, df_raw.columns)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Clean column names</span></span><span>
    df_clean = clean_column_names(df_raw)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Strip whitespace from text fields</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">for</span></span><span> col </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df_clean.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"object"</span></span><span>).columns:
        df_clean[col] = df_clean[col].</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip()

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Handle missing numeric values</span></span><span>
    df_clean = handle_missing_values(df_clean)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Remove invalid rows (negative prices/quantities)</span></span><span>
    df_clean = remove_invalid_rows(df_clean)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Save cleaned CSV</span></span><span>
    df_clean.to_csv(cleaned_path, index=</span><span><span class="hljs-literal">False</span></span><span>)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"Cleaning complete. First few rows:"</span></span><span>)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(df_clean.head())
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>

data_cleaning.py
Purpose:
    Loads messy sales data, cleans it, and writes cleaned output to data/processed.
"""</span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">import</span></span><span> pandas </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">as</span></span><span> pd

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted function</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">load_data</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">file_path: <span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Copilot-assisted function</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">clean_column_names</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    df.columns = (
        df.columns
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.lower()
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">" "</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
        .</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.replace(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"-"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"_"</span></span><span>)
    )
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Handles missing numeric values</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">handle_missing_values</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()
    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Drop rows where both price and qty are missing</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">and</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"qty"</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df.columns:
        df = df.dropna(subset=[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"qty"</span></span><span>], how=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"all"</span></span><span>)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Fill remaining numeric NaNs with 0</span></span><span>
    num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"number"</span></span><span>).columns
    df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(</span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df

</span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Removes invalid rows</span></span><span>
</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">def</span></span><span> </span><span><span class="hljs-title function_">remove_invalid_rows</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-params">df: pd.DataFrame</span></span><span>) -&gt; pd.DataFrame:
    df = df.copy()

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Convert numeric columns to proper types</span></span><span>
    df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>] = pd.to_numeric(df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>], errors=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"coerce"</span></span><span>)
    df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"qty"</span></span><span>] = pd.to_numeric(df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"qty"</span></span><span>], errors=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"coerce"</span></span><span>)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Remove rows with missing or negative values</span></span><span>
    df = df.dropna(subset=[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"qty"</span></span><span>])
    df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"price"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]
    df = df[df[</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"qty"</span></span><span>] &gt;= </span><span><span class="hljs-number">0</span></span><span>]

    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">return</span></span><span> df


</span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">if</span></span><span> __name__ == </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"__main__"</span></span><span>:
    raw_path = </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"data/raw/sales_data_raw.csv"</span></span><span>
    cleaned_path = </span><span><span class="hljs-string">"data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv"</span></span><span>

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Load raw data</span></span><span>
    df_raw = load_data(raw_path)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"Columns in CSV:"</span></span><span>, df_raw.columns)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Clean column names</span></span><span>
    df_clean = clean_column_names(df_raw)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Strip leading/trailing whitespace and lowercase text</span></span><span>
    </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">for</span></span><span> col </span><span><span class="hljs-keyword">in</span></span><span> df_clean.select_dtypes(include=</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"object"</span></span><span>).columns:
        df_clean[col] = df_clean[col].</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.strip().</span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">str</span></span><span>.lower()

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Handle missing numeric values</span></span><span>
    df_clean = handle_missing_values(df_clean)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Remove invalid rows (negative prices/qty)</span></span><span>
    df_clean = remove_invalid_rows(df_clean)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-comment"># Save cleaned CSV</span></span><span>
    df_clean.to_csv(cleaned_path, index=</span><span><span class="hljs-literal">False</span></span><span>)

    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(</span><span><span class="hljs-string">"Cleaning complete. First few rows:"</span></span><span>)
    </span><span><span class="hljs-built_in">print</span></span><span>(df_clean.head())
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>

<h3 data-start="2401" data-end="2422"> What this does:</h3>
<ol data-start="2424" data-end="2776">
<li data-start="2424" data-end="2447">
<p data-start="2427" data-end="2447">Loads the messy CSV.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2448" data-end="2531">
<p data-start="2451" data-end="2531">Standardizes column names (<code data-start="2478" data-end="2488">prodname</code>, <code data-start="2490" data-end="2500">category</code>, <code data-start="2502" data-end="2509">price</code>, <code data-start="2511" data-end="2516">qty</code>, <code data-start="2518" data-end="2529">date_sold</code>).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2532" data-end="2584">
<p data-start="2535" data-end="2584">Strips whitespace and lowercases all text fields.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2585" data-end="2626">
<p data-start="2588" data-end="2626">Converts <code data-start="2597" data-end="2604">price</code> and <code data-start="2609" data-end="2614">qty</code> to numeric.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2627" data-end="2675">
<p data-start="2630" data-end="2675">Removes rows with missing or negative values.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2676" data-end="2739">
<p data-start="2679" data-end="2739">Writes cleaned CSV to <code data-start="2701" data-end="2738">data/processed/sales_data_clean.csv</code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2740" data-end="2776">
<p data-start="2743" data-end="2776">Prints a preview of cleaned data.</p>
</li>
</ol>

Project</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What Copilot generated</span></span><span>
I used GitHub Copilot to generate the </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`load_data`</span></span><span> and </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`clean_column_names`</span></span><span> functions. I prompted Copilot with comments describing what I wanted each function to do, such as loading a CSV into a DataFrame and cleaning column names by stripping whitespace and converting to lowercase.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What I modified</span></span><span>
I modified the Copilot-generated code by adding handling for missing numeric values and invalid rows. For example, I converted the </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`price`</span></span><span> and </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`qty`</span></span><span> columns to numeric, removed negative values, and stripped and lowercased all text fields. I also fixed indentation issues and ensured that the cleaned CSV is written to the correct folder.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What I learned</span></span><span>
I learned that Pandas is very powerful for cleaning messy datasets, especially using </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`pd.to_numeric`</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`dropna`</span></span><span>, and conditional filtering. I also learned that Copilot is helpful for generating boilerplate code quickly, but it often needs refinement to handle real-world data issues, such as unexpected whitespace, negative values, or incorrect column names. Testing and inspecting data step-by-step is crucial to ensure correctness.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## Challenges and Improvements</span></span><span>
One challenge I faced was handling unexpected whitespace and capitalization in column names and text fields. I also encountered a TypeError when comparing strings to numbers, which taught me the importance of converting data to the correct type. In the future, I could further improve the script by standardizing product names and removing duplicates automatically.
</span></span></code></div></div></pre>

Project</span></span><span>

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What Copilot generated</span></span><span>
I used GitHub Copilot to generate the </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`load_data`</span></span><span> and </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`clean_column_names`</span></span><span> functions. I prompted Copilot with comments describing what I wanted each function to do, such as loading a CSV file into a pandas DataFrame and cleaning column names by stripping whitespace, converting to lowercase, and replacing spaces and dashes with underscores. Copilot provided a solid starting point for these functions, allowing me to focus on the more complex cleaning steps.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What I modified</span></span><span>
I modified the Copilot-generated code extensively to handle real-world issues in the dataset. For example, I added a function to handle missing numeric values by filling NaNs with zero or dropping rows where both </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`price`</span></span><span> and </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`qty`</span></span><span> were missing. I also created a function to remove invalid rows, converting </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`price`</span></span><span> and </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`qty`</span></span><span> to numeric types, removing negative values, and handling NaNs. I fixed indentation errors and updated the loop that cleans text fields to strip extra spaces and convert text to lowercase consistently. These changes ensured that the cleaned dataset was accurate and ready to use.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## What I learned</span></span><span>
Through this project, I learned how powerful Pandas is for data cleaning, including using </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`pd.to_numeric`</span></span><span>, </span><span><span class="hljs-code">`dropna`</span></span><span>, filtering with conditions, and cleaning text data. I also learned that GitHub Copilot is a helpful tool for generating boilerplate code quickly, but it requires careful review and modification to handle real-world datasets correctly. This project reinforced the importance of testing at each step and inspecting the data to catch issues such as extra whitespace, inconsistent capitalization, missing values, or invalid numeric entries.

</span><span><span class="hljs-section">## Challenges and Improvements</span></span><span>
One of the main challenges I faced was handling the inconsistent column names and whitespace in both the headers and the values themselves. I also encountered errors when numeric comparisons were attempted on string data, which taught me the importance of converting columns to the correct types before performing operations. In the future, I could further improve the script by standardizing product names, handling duplicates, or adding automated checks for unusual values.
